<h1 align="center"> 
Mobile ASP.NET Web Applications</h1> 


<body>


<blockquote>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p><b>Challenges of Mobile Web Devices</b></p>
  <ul>
    <li><span class="normal">Various markup languages required</span><ul>
      <li><span class="normal">&nbsp;HTML for PDAs</span></li>
      <li><span class="normal">WML (wireless markup language ) for WAP (wireless 
      application protocol) cell phones</span></li>
      <li><span class="normal">cHTML (compact HTML) for Japanese i-mode phones</span></li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    <li><span class="normal">Various form factors</span><ul>
      <li><span class="normal">Horizontal/vertical screen orientation</span></li>
      <li><span class="normal">Varying numbers of display lines permitted</span></li>
      <li><span class="normal">Color or black &amp; white displays</span></li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    <li><span class="normal">Various network connectivity</span><ul>
      <li><span class="normal">From 9.6 KB cellular connections to 11 MB 
      Wireless LANs.</span></li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    <span class="normal">
    <li>Various capabilities<ul>
      <li>Display images</li>
      <li>Make phone calls</li>
      <li>Receive notification messages</li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    </span>
  </ul>
  <p><b><span class="normal">Web Matrix</span></b></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Provides the tools you need to quickly develop mobile Web applications</li>
    <li>Works for a wide variety of mobile browsers available today<ul>
      <li>Reduces the challenge of writing and maintaining numerous 
      web-applications for specific browsers</li>
    </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>
</blockquote>


